# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: BlackMonolith | Scene: TheBlackMonolithMage3
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Samayra was still asleep next to her."
    new "Samayra was still asleep next to her."

    old "Sarah had come to know her as a surprisingly heavy sleeper."
    new "Sarah had come to know her as a surprisingly heavy sleeper."

    old "She decided to get up out of bed and let Samayra sleep."
    new "She decided to get up out of bed and let Samayra sleep."

    old "Sarah woke the next morning. Her room was quiet, save for herself."
    new "Sarah woke the next morning. Her room was quiet, save for herself."

    old "She decided to get out of bed."
    new "She decided to get out of bed."

    old "Walking through her room, Sarah gathered up her clothes and got dressed."
    new "Walking through her room, Sarah gathered up her clothes and got dressed."

    old "When she finished gettting dressed, she headed for the door."
    new "When she finished gettting dressed, she headed for the door."

    old "She headed out through the hallway and made her way to the kitchen."
    new "She headed out through the hallway and made her way to the kitchen."

    old "Growing up in Castle Reinmeer, she'd been used to servants for most of her life."
    new "Growing up in Castle Reinmeer, she'd been used to servants for most of her life."

    old "But ever since she had begun studying under Xan, she had to learn how to take care of herself."
    new "But ever since she had begun studying under Xan, she had to learn how to take care of herself."

    old "She had been embarased for a brief moment, having to learn how to cook, but over time she had oddly learned to enjoy it."
    new "She had been embarased for a brief moment, having to learn how to cook, but over time she had oddly learned to enjoy it."

    old "The ritual of it every morning had a way of grounding her."
    new "The ritual of it every morning had a way of grounding her."

    old "She had barely gathered a few items from the pantry when she heard a voice."
    new "She had barely gathered a few items from the pantry when she heard a voice."

    old "Sarah spun around, caught by surprise."
    new "Sarah spun around, caught by surprise."

    old "She saw Metis sitting in a chair, feet up on the table, leaning back."
    new "She saw Metis sitting in a chair, feet up on the table, leaning back."

    old "A plate of partially eaten food was in front of him."
    new "A plate of partially eaten food was in front of him."

    old "I...you startled me."
    new "I...you startled me."

    old "It's alright, we just...we don't have a lot of visitors."
    new "It's alright, we just...we don't have a lot of visitors."

    old "Yeah...Xan can be that way. I think he was more made to be alone. I guess that explains why he so rarely takes on new students."
    new "Yeah...Xan can be that way. I think he was more made to be alone. I guess that explains why he so rarely takes on new students."

    old "Sarah frowned and gestured at his feet."
    new "Sarah frowned and gestured at his feet."

    old "You mind taking those off the table? I eat there."
    new "You mind taking those off the table? I eat there."

    old "Metis swung his legs off the table, back onto the floor."
    new "Metis swung his legs off the table, back onto the floor."

    old "Apologies again. I just spend so much time in this place, it instantly feels like home. I forget myself."
    new "Apologies again. I just spend so much time in this place, it instantly feels like home. I forget myself."

    old "He grinned as he stabbed at some food and brought it to his mouth."
    new "He grinned as he stabbed at some food and brought it to his mouth."

    old "Yeah...you said that."
    new "Yeah...you said that."

    old "You're a former student of Xan? I don't remember him mentioning you."
    new "You're a former student of Xan? I don't remember him mentioning you."

    old "Metis fake stabbed himself in the chest with his knife."
    new "Metis fake stabbed himself in the chest with his knife."

    old "I'm wounded to hear."
    new "I'm wounded to hear."

    old "Then he laughed."
    new "Then he laughed."

    old "No, I guess Xan wouldn't be the type to talk about that. Ever so private."
    new "No, I guess Xan wouldn't be the type to talk about that. Ever so private."

    old "He didn't really tell me much about the order at all, really."
    new "He didn't really tell me much about the order at all, really."

    old "She saw him raise an eyebrow."
    new "She saw him raise an eyebrow."

    old "You want to learn more about the order?"
    new "You want to learn more about the order?"

    old "Sarah wondered if he genuinely offered to tell her, or if he was gauging how much she was drawing information out of him."
    new "Sarah wondered if he genuinely offered to tell her, or if he was gauging how much she was drawing information out of him."

    old "She had to be careful. Not too eager."
    new "She had to be careful. Not too eager."

    old "Only if you feel like telling me, I'm sure Xan will get around to it in time, when I'm ready."
    new "Only if you feel like telling me, I'm sure Xan will get around to it in time, when I'm ready."

    old "When you're ready, ooh sure."
    new "When you're ready, ooh sure."

    old "What is that supposed to mean?"
    new "What is that supposed to mean?"

    old "Well, let's say there is a good reason Xan might not have mentioned me. We didn't really end on a good note."
    new "Well, let's say there is a good reason Xan might not have mentioned me. We didn't really end on a good note."

    old "Sarah continued preparing her breakfast, hoping to appear disintrested."
    new "Sarah continued preparing her breakfast, hoping to appear disintrested."

    old "Ooh. Why is that?"
    new "Ooh. Why is that?"

    old "Well, like you said. Xan likes to decide the tempo. Decide when you're ready. When you're not."
    new "Well, like you said. Xan likes to decide the tempo. Decide when you're ready. When you're not."

    old "For a while I was studying under him and that worked fine. But after several years, I told him I wanted to run, not walk."
    new "For a while I was studying under him and that worked fine. But after several years, I told him I wanted to run, not walk."

    old "Metis stabbed at a piece of sausage, the grease shooting out as the fork punctured the skin."
    new "Metis stabbed at a piece of sausage, the grease shooting out as the fork punctured the skin."

    old "But Xan was always pushing back. So eventually, I said I was going to leave and continue my studies on my own."
    new "But Xan was always pushing back. So eventually, I said I was going to leave and continue my studies on my own."

    old "He wasn't a big fan of that."
    new "He wasn't a big fan of that."

    old "Yeah, he wanted me to study at the Citadel, but I can't say I was much up for that."
    new "Yeah, he wanted me to study at the Citadel, but I can't say I was much up for that."

    old "Heard the bored teachers go about poking the students there. No thank you."
    new "Heard the bored teachers go about poking the students there. No thank you."

    old "Metis made a disgusted face."
    new "Metis made a disgusted face."

    old "Metis raised an eyebrow."
    new "Metis raised an eyebrow."

    old "You never got that vibe from him? You've been his student for a few years now, right?"
    new "You never got that vibe from him? You've been his student for a few years now, right?"

    old "Yeah, there about."
    new "Yeah, there about."

    old "But I guess I can understand what you're saying. He does like to dictate the pace."
    new "But I guess I can understand what you're saying. He does like to dictate the pace."

    old "Ooh, more than just a teacher's pet. Who knew you had it in you."
    new "Ooh, more than just a teacher's pet. Who knew you had it in you."

    old "Sarah looked at him and shrugged."
    new "Sarah looked at him and shrugged."

    old "You really don't know me at all."
    new "You really don't know me at all."

    old "That's true, but I'd like to."
    new "That's true, but I'd like to."

    old "Well, I'm sure you have other affairs to see to. You strike me as a busy man."
    new "Well, I'm sure you have other affairs to see to. You strike me as a busy man."

    old "Metis leaned back in his chair."
    new "Metis leaned back in his chair."

    old "Truth is I'm rather lazy, and actually don't have much to do at the moment."
    new "Truth is I'm rather lazy, and actually don't have much to do at the moment."

    old "At least, not with Xan being absent, sadly."
    new "At least, not with Xan being absent, sadly."

    old "And my ship won't be pulling into harbor for at least a month, so not much I can do for the moment."
    new "And my ship won't be pulling into harbor for at least a month, so not much I can do for the moment."

    old "A month. Was he really planning to stay here that long? Then again, if he did, could she really throw him out?"
    new "A month. Was he really planning to stay here that long? Then again, if he did, could she really throw him out?"

    old "Doing so would only seem more suspicious."
    new "Doing so would only seem more suspicious."

    old "Where are you going? Perhaps the house can be of service. It's many doors can lead to many places."
    new "Where are you going? Perhaps the house can be of service. It's many doors can lead to many places."

    old "Yes, it's a useful thing this house."
    new "Yes, it's a useful thing this house."

    old "Then he shook his head."
    new "Then he shook his head."

    old "But I'm afraid it doesn't go everywhere. It's especially poorly connected to areas with little civilization."
    new "But I'm afraid it doesn't go everywhere. It's especially poorly connected to areas with little civilization."

    old "Sarah watched him, continue to eat."
    new "Sarah watched him, continue to eat."

    old "Where are you going?"
    new "Where are you going?"

    old "Metis didn't answer, continuing to eat as if he had not heard her. She was quite sure he had."
    new "Metis didn't answer, continuing to eat as if he had not heard her. She was quite sure he had."

    old "So anyway, I'm stuck out here in Lethram for a month."
    new "So anyway, I'm stuck out here in Lethram for a month."

    old "I hope I wouldn't ask too much of you by asking if I can stay?"
    new "I hope I wouldn't ask too much of you by asking if I can stay?"

    old "I can see if Xan comes home."
    new "I can see if Xan comes home."

    old "Sarah kept his eyes. She wasn't sure what she saw in them. Did he know anything. Was he genuinely wondering?"
    new "Sarah kept his eyes. She wasn't sure what she saw in them. Did he know anything. Was he genuinely wondering?"

    old "Well, like I said, he's gone for weeks or months, I can't say he'll be back."
    new "Well, like I said, he's gone for weeks or months, I can't say he'll be back."

    old "But you're more than welcome to stay for as long as you like."
    new "But you're more than welcome to stay for as long as you like."

    old "Metis gave a wide smile."
    new "Metis gave a wide smile."

    old "A most kind host. I promise I won't inconvenience you."
    new "A most kind host. I promise I won't inconvenience you."

    old "He suddenly slammed the table with an open palm."
    new "He suddenly slammed the table with an open palm."

    old "If anything, how about I make it worth your while."
    new "If anything, how about I make it worth your while."

    old "Worth my while? How?"
    new "Worth my while? How?"

    old "Well, I'm a mage with a fair bit of experience."
    new "Well, I'm a mage with a fair bit of experience."

    old "I'm not quite on Xan's level, but I have researched a few obscure areas that might be interesting to you."
    new "I'm not quite on Xan's level, but I have researched a few obscure areas that might be interesting to you."

    old "I know Xan can get stuck on the basics. Floating, fire, maybe teleporting. All a bit mundane after a while."
    new "I know Xan can get stuck on the basics. Floating, fire, maybe teleporting. All a bit mundane after a while."

    old "Sarah eyed him."
    new "Sarah eyed him."

    old "His offer was interesting. It was true that she'd wondered how she could best continue her studies now that Xan was gone."
    new "His offer was interesting. It was true that she'd wondered how she could best continue her studies now that Xan was gone."

    old "Perhaps this man was a possible solution."
    new "Perhaps this man was a possible solution."

    old "What could you teach me, exactly?"
    new "What could you teach me, exactly?"

    old "He smiled, realizing she was interested."
    new "He smiled, realizing she was interested."

    old "Well, I'm quite proficient with Botany and Transmogrification."
    new "Well, I'm quite proficient with Botany and Transmogrification."

    old "Then there is also Daemonology, but Xan really wouldn't like you to study that, so I'd hestiate to even offer."
    new "Then there is also Daemonology, but Xan really wouldn't like you to study that, so I'd hestiate to even offer."

    old "Sarah smiled. His trickery was subtle yet blatant."
    new "Sarah smiled. His trickery was subtle yet blatant."

    old "If he had actually never wanted her to ask about Daemonology, he could have simply never mentioned it. Instead he had."
    new "If he had actually never wanted her to ask about Daemonology, he could have simply never mentioned it. Instead he had."

    old "Sarah considered for a moment what her best answer would be."
    new "Sarah considered for a moment what her best answer would be."

    old "Botany would offer many advantages outside of simply magic. She had never learned as much about potions as she'd wanted from Xan."
    new "Botany would offer many advantages outside of simply magic. She had never learned as much about potions as she'd wanted from Xan."

    old "In addition, she'd always had a natural affinity for plants."
    new "In addition, she'd always had a natural affinity for plants."

    old "Transmogrification was the art of transforming the body. Xan had warned her of the risks and always told her to stay away from such studies."
    new "Transmogrification was the art of transforming the body. Xan had warned her of the risks and always told her to stay away from such studies."

    old "Lastly, Daemonology was a field Sarah was almost entirely unfamiliar with."
    new "Lastly, Daemonology was a field Sarah was almost entirely unfamiliar with."

    old "Xan had only spoken of it on a few occasions, always dismissive."
    new "Xan had only spoken of it on a few occasions, always dismissive."

    old "Study Botany"
    new "Study Botany"

    old "I would like to study Botany."
    new "I would like to study Botany."

    old "Study Transmogrification"
    new "Study Transmogrification"

    old "I would like to study Transmogrification."
    new "I would like to study Transmogrification."

    old "Study Daemonology"
    new "Study Daemonology"

    old "I would like to study Daemonology."
    new "I would like to study Daemonology."

    old "Metis smiled at her answer."
    new "Metis smiled at her answer."

    old "A good choice."
    new "A good choice."

    old "Botany forms the basis of any good mage in my view."
    new "Botany forms the basis of any good mage in my view."

    old "Too many rely exclusively on their magical potential, neglecting entire branches of study."
    new "Too many rely exclusively on their magical potential, neglecting entire branches of study."

    old "Do you know much about it?"
    new "Do you know much about it?"

    old "Better than most, but there are a few out there that put me to shame. Still, enough to give you a decent foundation."
    new "Better than most, but there are a few out there that put me to shame. Still, enough to give you a decent foundation."

    old "I'll draft up some study materials and we can schedule a first lesson later this week."
    new "I'll draft up some study materials and we can schedule a first lesson later this week."

    old "I'll look forward to it."
    new "I'll look forward to it."

    old "Transmogrification is a dangerous field, but it offers plenty of rewards."
    new "Transmogrification is a dangerous field, but it offers plenty of rewards."

    old "No wonder Xan never wanted you to learn about it. He was the same with me."
    new "No wonder Xan never wanted you to learn about it. He was the same with me."

    old "That's an interesting choice. But I'm not sure that Xan would approve."
    new "That's an interesting choice. But I'm not sure that Xan would approve."

    old "Sarah kept her eyes on him. His body language didn't seem to give much away."
    new "Sarah kept her eyes on him. His body language didn't seem to give much away."

    old "Well, you offered."
    new "Well, you offered."

    old "Did I? I think I said that I'd hestitate to offer it."
    new "Did I? I think I said that I'd hestitate to offer it."

    old "A reluctant offer is still an offer."
    new "A reluctant offer is still an offer."

    old "Well, fair enough. If you're going to twist my arm on the matter, I'll teach you."
    new "Well, fair enough. If you're going to twist my arm on the matter, I'll teach you."

    old "Just remember, it's dangerous stuff. Not a joke. If I teach you this, you can't ever practice it without my supervision."
    new "Just remember, it's dangerous stuff. Not a joke. If I teach you this, you can't ever practice it without my supervision."

    old "Metis sighed."
    new "Metis sighed."

    old "I guess I'll go ahead and gather up some study materials then. We can schedule a first lesson later this week."
    new "I guess I'll go ahead and gather up some study materials then. We can schedule a first lesson later this week."

    old "Do you know much about this topic?"
    new "Do you know much about this topic?"

    old "Metis got up and looked at her, smiling."
    new "Metis got up and looked at her, smiling."

    old "I'm actually the world's most foremost expert on the field."
    new "I'm actually the world's most foremost expert on the field."

    old "With that, Metis turned to leave."
    new "With that, Metis turned to leave."

    old "Sarah sat down at the kitchen table with her own plate of food."
    new "Sarah sat down at the kitchen table with her own plate of food."

    old "She had eaten about half her plate of food when she heard soft sounds coming down the hall."
    new "She had eaten about half her plate of food when she heard soft sounds coming down the hall."

    old "If she hadn't known better, she could have mistaken the sound for mice."
    new "If she hadn't known better, she could have mistaken the sound for mice."

    old "Instead, she knew it to be Samayra."
    new "Instead, she knew it to be Samayra."

    old "Good morning."
    new "Good morning."

    old "The girl smiled as she walked into the kitchen."
    new "The girl smiled as she walked into the kitchen."

    old "She was still rubbing her eyes free from the sleep."
    new "She was still rubbing her eyes free from the sleep."

    old "Samayra sat down at the table next to Sarah."
    new "Samayra sat down at the table next to Sarah."

    old "You had a good night sleep?"
    new "You had a good night sleep?"

    old "Sleeping next to you is always better."
    new "Sleeping next to you is always better."

    old "My own bed is nice but it's...too big. If it's just me, there is just too much space."
    new "My own bed is nice but it's...too big. If it's just me, there is just too much space."

    old "Well, you know that I don't mind, right? I know this place and all...it's new for you."
    new "Well, you know that I don't mind, right? I know this place and all...it's new for you."

    old "I remember how it was when I first got here. It can be a lonely place. I don't want it to be that for you."
    new "I remember how it was when I first got here. It can be a lonely place. I don't want it to be that for you."

    old "I know, and it doesn't feel lonely when you're here."
    new "I know, and it doesn't feel lonely when you're here."

    old "Sarah was happy to hear her say that."
    new "Sarah was happy to hear her say that."

    old "And I still think about home a lot too, but I guess I just try to make the best of it, you know?"
    new "And I still think about home a lot too, but I guess I just try to make the best of it, you know?"

    old "I guess I get to see more of the world, so it's not all bad."
    new "I guess I get to see more of the world, so it's not all bad."

    old "Sarah watched as the girl gave her another smile, but there seemed to be hints of pain behind it."
    new "Sarah watched as the girl gave her another smile, but there seemed to be hints of pain behind it."

    old "Still, she didn't want to press her too much. Samayra would talk to her if she was ready."
    new "Still, she didn't want to press her too much. Samayra would talk to her if she was ready."

    old "I was rolling around in my own bed all night."
    new "I was rolling around in my own bed all night."

    old "It's way too big for someone my size. Too much space."
    new "It's way too big for someone my size. Too much space."

    old "Well, sorry to hear that. Maybe we can find you a different bed."
    new "Well, sorry to hear that. Maybe we can find you a different bed."

    old "Or maybe we could fill up some of the space in my bed."
    new "Or maybe we could fill up some of the space in my bed."

    old "Samayra threw a meaningful look at Sarah."
    new "Samayra threw a meaningful look at Sarah."

    old "Samayra...you know that I didn't mean anything by it...I just..."
    new "Samayra...you know that I didn't mean anything by it...I just..."

    old "I know, I'm sorry if I sound whiny. It was just...you were gone and I was in this house all alone."
    new "I know, I'm sorry if I sound whiny. It was just...you were gone and I was in this house all alone."

    old "I hope that when you got back we could...catch up."
    new "I hope that when you got back we could...catch up."

    old "Sarah reached out and grabbed the girl's hand."
    new "Sarah reached out and grabbed the girl's hand."

    old "Hey, don't worry. We will. I promise."
    new "Hey, don't worry. We will. I promise."

    old "This seemed to restore some hapiness in her, a smile creeping on Samayra's face."
    new "This seemed to restore some hapiness in her, a smile creeping on Samayra's face."

    old "Suddenly, Sarah watched as Samayra drove a fork into one of her panckes and quickly shoved it into her own mouth."
    new "Suddenly, Sarah watched as Samayra drove a fork into one of her panckes and quickly shoved it into her own mouth."

    old "Hey! That's my breakfast! Go make your own!"
    new "Hey! That's my breakfast! Go make your own!"

    old "Too slow!"
    new "Too slow!"

    old "Samayra spoke while her mouth was still full of food."
    new "Samayra spoke while her mouth was still full of food."

    old "Her fork shot out and claimed more of Sarah's food."
    new "Her fork shot out and claimed more of Sarah's food."

    old "Sarah grabbed the plate and pulled it out of reach of Samayra."
    new "Sarah grabbed the plate and pulled it out of reach of Samayra."

    old "You're awful!"
    new "You're awful!"

    old "The two former princesses spend the rest of their morning together."
    new "The two former princesses spend the rest of their morning together."

    old "As they ate breakfast, Sarah shared as much as she could for the moment about her experience in Nauyziri."
    new "As they ate breakfast, Sarah shared as much as she could for the moment about her experience in Nauyziri."

    old "Samayra, for her part, clinged to every word from Sarah's lips."
    new "Samayra, for her part, clinged to every word from Sarah's lips."

    old "Sarah couldn't explain how happy it made her to have someone to talk with. Someone who cared."
    new "Sarah couldn't explain how happy it made her to have someone to talk with. Someone who cared."

    old "She ate her breakfast in peaceful silence."
    new "She ate her breakfast in peaceful silence."

